rough sheep
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:  1
Definition:a sheep that has missed a docking, shearing or muster and is often wild.


Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain: Rural
Region: [none]
See: double-fleecer; double-decker; hermit; long tailer
Pronunciation:
Notes:
